{
  "document_id": "judg-5",
  "title": "Judges 5",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-heading-the-song-of-deborah",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "The Song of Deborah"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then Deborah and Barak son of Abinoam sang on that day,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“When locks are long in Israel,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Hear, O kings; give ear, O princes;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Lord, when you went out from Seir,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "The mountains quaked before the Lord, the One of Sinai,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "In the days of Shamgar son of Anath,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "The peasantry prospered in Israel;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "When new gods were chosen,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "My heart goes out to the commanders of Israel"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Sing of it, you who ride on white donkeys,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "To the sound of musicians at the watering places,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Awake, awake, Deborah!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Then down marched the remnant of the nobles;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "From Ephraim they set out into the valley,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "the chiefs of Issachar came with Deborah,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Why did you tarry among the sheepfolds,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Gilead stayed beyond the Jordan,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Zebulun is a people that scorned death;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "The kings came; they fought;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "The stars fought from heaven;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "The torrent Kishon swept them away,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Then loud beat the horses’ hoofs"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Curse Meroz, says the angel of the Lord;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Most blessed of women be Jael,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Water he asked, milk she gave;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "She put her hand to the tent peg"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "Between her feet he sank, he fell,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Out of the window she peered;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Her wisest ladies make answer;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "‘Are they not finding and dividing the spoil?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "judg-5-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "So perish all your enemies, O Lord!"
    }
  ]
}